other_tests.findings: Within 7 hours, symptoms of dizziness and lethargy appeared. Glucose level was 43 mg per deciliter (2.4 mmol per liter), and insulin level was 12 Î¼IU per milliliter.
Revealed acinar and columnar pancreatic cells with positive staining for synapto-physin, chromogranin, and insulin.

other_tests.procedure_name: Open enucleation of the pancreatic insulinoma
other_tests.findings: Mass was a pancreatic endocrine tumor; it measured 1.5 by 1.0 by 0.8 cm and had clean margins.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Patient recovered rapidly and remained asymptomatic and normoglycemic 1 year after the surgery.
